The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Aug. 29 (PTI): Singer Adnan Sami, accused of cruelty and cheating by wife Sabah Galadari, was arrested last night and later granted bail.           
	Sami was called to Oshiwara police station and asked to give two sureties of Rs 15,000 each, his lawyer Vibhav Krishna said today.           
	The singer had earlier moved Bombay High Court, which had granted him anticipatory bail.           
	Sabah had lodged the case claiming Sami had tried to throw her out of their house. She had also accused the singer of an extramarital affair                  
	 Bhopal (PTI): The Madhya Pradesh governments food department on Saturday raided two godowns in Mandideep town near Bhopal and seized 6,670 quintals of sugar. The government has seized 10,760 quintals of sugar in a drive against hoarders and blackmarketeers in the last 15days.                  
	Kanpur (PTI): A 14-year-old boy has gone missing, apparently unhappy with his parents relocating to Kanpur from Lakhimpur. Pratul, his parents said in a police complaint, did not return from school on August 26. The police said they did not think it was a case of kidnapping as no one has demanded a ransom.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Centre said on Saturday it was planning to organise a book fair in the US next year. We will explore the possibility of holding a book fair in the Bay area (California) where a lot of NRIs live. There is a lot of interest in Indian books in the US, said Subas Pani, chairman of the Indian Trade Promotion Organisation.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): Two HIV-infected children, under treatment at a hospital here, will be discharged for a few days so that they can celebrate Onam with their grandmother at their home in Kollam. The parents of the children had died of AIDS a few years back.                                                                                                                           
